    had been standing. She ran \u2014 and thought while she ran, which was the most
    important thing she could have done."
  - Because across the chamber, a sword floated on a narrow pillar of pale stone.
  - "Its design was different from any Egyptian blade \u2014 broader at the hilt,
    with a crossguard bearing colonial-era engraving, the kind found on ceremonial
    weapons of the Southern Hemisphere's founding age. And yet it sat here as though
    it had always belonged."
  - "\u2726  The Sword of Macquarie. Like Excalibur, it cannot be taken by force.
    It waits not for the strongest, but for the one who thinks deeply enough to deserve
    it."
  textSpeed: 0.05
  playerTag: Player
  triggerOnce: 1
